text:
I received this product for free to review as part of Sundown Vitamin's 7-Day Experience. 

I was a little skeptical about the sleep claims for melatonin but I received my sample package during a week where my sleeping patterns were off and I was having a little trouble going to sleep so I thought the timing was great. It could have been a placebo effect, but I think these did work for me. I found myself being able to fall asleep right away and wake rested. I've never had problems staying asleep so I can't say if melatonin would have any effect on that.

These were very easy to take and tasty. The only issue I really have is that they're gummies so I need to brush my teeth after taking them and depending on my schedule, that's sometimes a bit of a pain.  While I would definitely recommend these to people looking for a natural way to improve their sleep, I think I might prefer my melatonin in a pill form so I could brush my teeth early and not need to brush again after taking it.

text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] This was my first time using Melatonin after hearing great things about it. I took on 10mg tablet, it dissolved fast, but it definitely didn't do the trick of knocking me out in 20 minutes, or a few hours for that matter.  However, on second run and forward, 2 tablets for this big man and I'm sleeping very soundly, very quickly, and very restfully.  All in the right portions!  I'm a large person and I don't think I'd recommend doubling the dose, I'm certainly not a medical professional, but I do know what works for me.  This does!

text:
Pay attention to what you're buying. I don't know why this product is labeled the way it is. You get 120 gummies, but there are not 120 servings.
I took one of these gummies and was wondering why they didn't work nearly as well as the melatonin I'm accustomed to using. After two nights with not so great sleep, I thought maybe the melatonin half-life was briefer in the gummy. Then, I realized I was taking 2.5 mg, not 5, because there are only 2.5 mg of melatonin per gummy. Taking two gummies fixed the issue.
I like that they are sugar free, they taste fine (strawberry), and they aren't too chewy in texture so that they will be easy for people who need to be gentle on their teeth. The expiration date on the one I got is about 13.5 months away, so plenty of time to use them all.
They are definitely a good alternative to the small melatonin tablets for someone who absolutely cannot swallow pills. They are also great for people who decide they need a 2.5 mg serving of melatonin.

productName: Zarbee's Children's Sleep Chewable Tablet with Melatonin, Grape, 30 Ct
text: I use these for myself because they are one of the only 1mg of melatonin I can find. People need to dive into melatonin dosage research more. I'm an adult and overweight if you want to consider weight factor into dosage and when I do take this, I take half a tablet (0.5mg). I never wake up groggy after taking half a tablet and it gives me enough push to fall asleep. On 3mg  I tend to have nightmares and wake up groggy. I imagine it's the same for many adults and children but it's not widely known that melatonin should be taken in extremely small dosages because many tablets are 5mg-10mg. You and your child should be taking the smallest dose possible to help you fall asleep, not make you fall asleep. As far as this brand, I love it. I like the ingredients and although I think their dosage recommendations are too high, they're a lot better than the 10mg gummies people eat like snacks.

text: I have had really good luck with this version of Melatonin. I have tried the Spring Valley regular 5mg and wasn't as happy. I take this 2 hrs before I go to bed and very rarely do I not sleep through the night even falling back asleep quickly typically if I get up to use the bathroom. I am however on Trazodone for insomnia which I'm sure helps. I started this almost a year ago after taking care of my father before he passed. I was up every 2 hours to give him pain medication and this screwed up my sleeping even after he had passed. Melatonin was suggested to straighten my sleep out by my Psych nurse practitioner. She said no more than 5 mg and at least two hours before bed. So after shopping around I found this at the store. I chose the fast dissolve and the rest was history. Since the pandemic even though the app said this was available at my store it wasn't so I bought the regular 5 mg and just didn't have the same luck. I moved to a tropical environment and the light seems much brighter.   From the moment I got here my sleeping pattern altered.  So I tried this on a nurse's recommendation.

Works, but I'm concerned it interferes with natural production.    I need to read up on it. If I forget to take it, the next thing I know, I'm up to the wee hours, still awake.

Will give you a morning foggy brain that takes a little time to shake.  

In general and as a lifestyle I avoid pharmaceuticals because they typically have risks greater than benefits.   So, as that type of person, and the fact my natural sleep appears to wane with this use, I only recommend caution and looking into before you adopt this.  Use it or loose it is a biological fact, so I have concerns that taking this might give me issues I didn't have before.   I might just need a black out curtain.   ;)

Make peace with what worries you.  Turn off the tv and internet anti-social media…before you resort to chemicals to sleep.

productName: Mommy's Bliss Kids Sleep Gummies with Melatonin, Strawberry, 3+ Years, 66 ct.
text:
I have used quite a few mommy's bliss products, they are affordable high quality products. These melatonin gummies taste great, they do contain 1gram of sugar (per gummy I believe) good to know. My toddler doesn't have issues getting to sleep at home but on overnight trips she can never fall asleep so these 1mg dose gummies are perfect for those occasions. They are not intended for everyday use, I think they can leave you feeling groggy in the mornings if you over do it. 
They look exactly like gummies so you might want to keep the bottle away from children. My daughter saw them on the counter and asked if she could have ‘a gummy bear'. So in the medicine cabinet they went.
title: Taste great.

productName: Mommy's Bliss Kids Sleep Gummies with Melatonin, Strawberry, 3+ Years, 66 ct.
text: I received the mommy Bliss kids sleep gummies with melatonin for 3-year-olds and up for my honest review. I have to say the first night I got them I tried them out myself and they were good. They had a delicious flavor, just like candy. I took 3 of them right before bed laid and checked some emails on my phone and about 20 to 30min later they really hadn't done anything so I took two more and they seem to relax me. I didn't so much feel sleepy but I felt relaxed to where, not even knowing I just closed my eyes and off too sleep I went. Usually I have to go on my phone or listen to music so I'm not paying there for hours thinking about all I have to do tomorrow. Usually playing light music helps. After taking these I was laying there thinking ok if they don't do nothing I'm going to play some music and before I knew it, it was morning. I usually don't get up during the night so I slept like a baby lol. I woke up and felt like I normally do so they didn't give me a groggy feeling that other sleeping aids I've tried did. All in all I'd say if they worked for me an adult they should work for your little ones at the recommended dose. I haven't tried them yet because I'm waiting for one of those restless nights. It doesn't happen often but once in a while my kids will have trouble falling asleep and I think one or two of these would come in handy. I do recommend these because they relax you to the point you just doze off to sleep. They don't knock you out or make you feel really sleepy with heavy eyes. I like them and if they seem to do the same for my kids as they did for me I'll be buying again.
title: Delicious flavor

The natural mint flavor is well-received, making the tablets pleasant to consume before bedtime. The minty taste is refreshing and helps mask any potential bitterness from the melatonin, enhancing the overall experience.
